      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. so basically you're saying \"controlled\" and \"sleek\" is the way to go. but for some of my employees with thicker, more natural hair textures, wouldn't a \"sleek blowout\" or a \"smooth\" look be really difficult or even feel like they're hiding who they are? i'm worried that if they don't follow that specific standard, they won't be taken as seriously as the ones with straighter hair. is that a real factor in how professionalism is perceived in those rooms?",
